{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Triagegeist — Signal Discovery\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks through the data analysis that shaped our solution.  \n",
    "The goal: understand what actually predicts emergency triage acuity (1–5) before writing any model code.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Spoiler:** the answer is mostly in plain text."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mtick\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='darkgrid', palette='muted')\n",
    "pd.set_option('display.max_columns', 50)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load data (assumes competition files are in ../data/)\n",
    "train = pd.read_csv('../data/train.csv')\n",
    "test  = pd.read_csv('../data/test.csv')\n",
    "complaints = pd.read_csv('../data/chief_complaints.csv')\n",
    "history    = pd.read_csv('../data/patient_history.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "train_c = train.merge(complaints[['patient_id','chief_complaint_raw']], on='patient_id', how='left')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Train: {train.shape}   Test: {test.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'Complaints: {complaints.shape}   History: {history.shape}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Target Distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "Triage acuity 1–5, where 1 is most critical. Class 3 (Urgent) dominates."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "labels = {1:'Critical', 2:'Emergent', 3:'Urgent', 4:'Less Urgent', 5:'Non-urgent'}\n",
    "counts = train['triage_acuity'].value_counts().sort_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
    "bars = ax.bar([f\"{k}\\n{labels[k]}\" for k in counts.index], counts.values, color=sns.color_palette('muted'))\n",
    "ax.bar_label(bars, fmt='{:,.0f}', padding=3)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Target Distribution — Triage Acuity', fontsize=14)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Count')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(counts.rename('count').to_frame().assign(pct=lambda d: (d['count']/len(train)*100).round(1)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Which numeric features correlate with acuity?\n",
    "\n",
    "NEWS2 score is almost perfectly predictive on its own."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "numeric = train.select_dtypes(include=[float, int]).drop(columns=['triage_acuity'])\n",
    "# Drop leakage columns not in test\n",
    "numeric = numeric.drop(columns=['ed_los_hours'], errors='ignore')\n",
    "corr = numeric.corrwith(train['triage_acuity']).abs().sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "corr.head(12).plot.barh(ax=ax, color='steelblue')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('|Pearson correlation with triage_acuity|')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Feature Correlations with Target', fontsize=14)\n",
    "ax.invert_yaxis()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. NEWS2 score vs acuity — almost deterministic\n",
    "\n",
    "NEWS2 (National Early Warning Score 2) is a clinical scoring system computed from vitals.\n",
    "High NEWS2 = high severity = low acuity number."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pivot = pd.crosstab(train['news2_score'], train['triage_acuity'], normalize='index')\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=ax, colormap='RdYlGn_r', width=0.85)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('NEWS2 Score')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Proportion')\n",
    "ax.set_title('NEWS2 Score → Triage Acuity (stacked proportions)', fontsize=14)\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mtick.PercentFormatter(1.0))\n",
    "ax.legend(title='Acuity', bbox_to_anchor=(1.01, 1), loc='upper left')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. The key discovery: chief complaint text\n",
    "\n",
    "How many unique complaint texts are there, and are they predictive?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"Unique complaint texts: {train_c['chief_complaint_raw'].nunique()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total rows: {len(train_c)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Avg rows per complaint text: {len(train_c) / train_c['chief_complaint_raw'].nunique():.1f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# How many texts are perfectly predictive (map to exactly 1 acuity)?\n",
    "text_acuity = train_c.groupby('chief_complaint_raw')['triage_acuity'].nunique()\n",
    "print(f\"\\nComplaint texts with exactly 1 acuity value: {(text_acuity == 1).sum()} ({100*(text_acuity==1).mean():.1f}%)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Complaint texts with 2+ acuity values:      {(text_acuity > 1).sum()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Coverage: what % of training rows are covered by unambiguous texts?\n",
    "unamb = text_acuity[text_acuity == 1].index\n",
    "coverage = train_c['chief_complaint_raw'].isin(unamb).mean()\n",
    "print(f\"\\nRows covered by unambiguous texts: {coverage:.1%}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Sample complaints and their acuity\n",
    "sample = train_c.groupby('chief_complaint_raw').agg(\n",
    "    acuity=('triage_acuity', lambda x: x.mode()[0]),\n",
    "    count=('triage_acuity', 'count')\n",
    ").reset_index().sort_values('acuity').groupby('acuity').head(3)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Sample complaint texts by acuity:\")\n",
    "print(sample[['acuity','chief_complaint_raw','count']].to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. TF-IDF scaling experiment\n",
    "\n",
    "This plot shows the CV accuracy at each TF-IDF feature count, reproducing the autoresearch log."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "experiments = [\n",
    "    {'features': 50,   'cv': 0.8910},\n",
    "    {'features': 150,  'cv': 0.9836},\n",
    "    {'features': 300,  'cv': 0.9919},\n",
    "    {'features': 500,  'cv': 0.9948},\n",
    "    {'features': 1000, 'cv': 0.9980},\n",
    "    {'features': 2000, 'cv': 0.9989},\n",
    "]\n",
    "df_exp = pd.DataFrame(experiments)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
    "ax.plot(df_exp['features'], df_exp['cv'], 'o-', color='steelblue', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "for _, row in df_exp.iterrows():\n",
    "    ax.annotate(f\"{row['cv']:.4f}\", (row['features'], row['cv']),\n",
    "                textcoords='offset points', xytext=(0, 10), ha='center', fontsize=9)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('TF-IDF max_features')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('CV Accuracy')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Scaling Chief Complaint TF-IDF Features → CV Accuracy', fontsize=13)\n",
    "ax.set_xscale('log')\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0.87, 1.001)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "total_vocab = 2995  # actual vocabulary size\n",
    "print(f\"Total vocabulary (bigrams, min_df=2): {total_vocab}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Score at 2000 features == score at full vocab — we've hit the ceiling\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Error analysis — tracing the 0.11% errors\n",
    "\n",
    "After model convergence, we ran full CV error analysis. Where are the mistakes coming from?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# All 15 ambiguous complaint texts\n",
    "ambiguous = text_acuity[text_acuity > 1]\n",
    "print(f\"Ambiguous complaint texts: {len(ambiguous)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Rows in ambiguous texts:   {train_c['chief_complaint_raw'].isin(ambiguous.index).sum()}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"The ambiguous texts:\")\n",
    "for txt in ambiguous.index:\n",
    "    sub = train_c[train_c['chief_complaint_raw'] == txt]\n",
    "    dist = sub['triage_acuity'].value_counts().sort_index().to_dict()\n",
    "    print(f\"  {txt[:60]:<60} → {dist}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Focus on glaucoma: acuity 1 vs 2 split by GCS\n",
    "gl = train_c[train_c['chief_complaint_raw'].str.contains('glaucoma', case=False, na=False)].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# GCS distribution by acuity\n",
    "for acuity, grp in gl.groupby('triage_acuity'):\n",
    "    axes[0].hist(grp['gcs_total'], bins=range(3, 16), alpha=0.6, label=f'Acuity {acuity}', density=True)\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('GCS Total')\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Density')\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Glaucoma: GCS by Acuity')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# NEWS2 distribution by acuity\n",
    "for acuity, grp in gl.groupby('triage_acuity'):\n",
    "    axes[1].hist(grp['news2_score'], bins=range(0, 19), alpha=0.6, label=f'Acuity {acuity}', density=True)\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('NEWS2 Score')\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Density')\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Glaucoma: NEWS2 by Acuity')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('Acute Angle Closure Glaucoma — Acuity 1 vs 2 Separation', fontsize=13)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nGlaucoma acuity distribution:\", gl['triage_acuity'].value_counts().sort_index().to_dict())\n",
    "print(f\"Acuity=1: mean GCS={gl[gl.triage_acuity==1]['gcs_total'].mean():.1f}, mean NEWS2={gl[gl.triage_acuity==1]['news2_score'].mean():.1f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Acuity=2: mean GCS={gl[gl.triage_acuity==2]['gcs_total'].mean():.1f}, mean NEWS2={gl[gl.triage_acuity==2]['news2_score'].mean():.1f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Missing values\n",
    "\n",
    "Vitals can be missing when patients arrive without prior measurement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "missing = train.isnull().sum()\n",
    "missing = missing[missing > 0].sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 3))\n",
    "missing.plot.barh(ax=ax, color='salmon')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Missing count')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Missing Values in Training Data', fontsize=13)\n",
    "ax.invert_yaxis()\n",
    "for i, v in enumerate(missing):\n",
    "    ax.text(v + 20, i, f'{v/len(train):.1%}', va='center', fontsize=9)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Chief complaint text** is the dominant signal. 99.4% of test rows can be answered with a lookup table.\n",
    "- **NEWS2 score** is the strongest numeric feature (0.81 correlation), but the text captures this implicitly.\n",
    "- **All remaining errors** trace to 15 "acute angle closure glaucoma" variants on the acuity 1/2 boundary.\n",
    "- **GCS and NEWS2 together** separate the glaucoma cases. A dedicated binary classifier on those 237 rows achieves 94% CV accuracy.\n",
    "\n",
    "See `src/generate_submission_final.py` for the full 3-tier prediction pipeline."
   ]
  }
 ],
